[1m[33m11:00 - 19:00[22m[34mLockton Executive Briefing - Day 1 Sessions[36mlocation:[39m 15975 NE One Microsoft Way, Redmond, Washington 98052, United States[36mnotes:[39m 8:30 – 9:00
Welcome to Microsoft Experience Center One
Lockton Leadership to provide an overview of objectives for the briefing, Lockton’s core priorities, and overall IT strategy.
Inside Microsoft - Microsoft Customer Experience Innovation Journey

Microsoft has applied years of research and market insights to develop a differentiated customer experience strategy, which is guiding the transformation of our own end-to-end customer experience delivery. Many of Microsoft’s customers are embarking on a similar journey, which has created a unique opportunity to bring together the thought leaders from these customer companies with the subject matter experts from Microsoft to co-create a unique and differentiated CX Innovation solution for their businesses.

This session will address Microsoft’s digital and cultural transformation. Given the current technology landscape, a primary focus will be the impact of AI and trends we are seeing across industries globally. In addition, we will share lessons learned related to our people and the broad impact of our culture transformation under Satya.
EVP, Chief Strategy and Transformation Officer
Future of AI at Work with Copilot

Copilot brings together Microsoft’s latest AI innovations, customer best practices, and industry insights to show how organizations can shift from personal‑productivity use cases to a unified, enterprise‑wide AI platform that improves productivity, governance, and long‑term innovation. It reframes AI at work by highlighting emerging trends, demonstrating new Copilot capabilities, and illustrating how companies can modernize workflows and scale value through agents and integrated enterprise data.

Learn how Microsoft Purview delivers comprehensive data security by integrating information protection, data loss prevention and insider risk management, and data security investigations together to help you understand and mitigate your data risks.
Vice President & General Manager, Data & AI Security

Microsoft Security Copilot is a generative AI-powered assistant for daily operations in security and IT. Copilot empowers teams to manage and protect at the speed and scale of AI by turning global threat intelligence, industry best practices, and organizations’ data from Microsoft and partner tools into tailored insights to respond faster and catch what others miss.
